What do HTML and CSS stand for?
Hyper Text Markup Language, Cascading Style Sheets

What do almost all HTML tags have?
Opening and closing tag

https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element

What are the three parts of an HTML element?
Opening tag, content, closing tag

Read up on https://www.theodinproject.com/lessons/foundations-the-box-model and https://www.theodinproject.com/lessons/foundations-block-and-inline

How do you setup a flexbox?
Have a parent class with child classes inside
EX:https://codepen.io/TheOdinProjectExamples/pen/QWgNxrp

A flex container is any element that contains what?
display: flex

What goes inside a flex container?
flex-items

https://cdn.statically.io/gh/TheOdinProject/curriculum/495704c6eb6bf33bc927534f231533a82b27b2ac/html_css/v2/foundations/flexbox/imgs/03.png

What is flex shorthand for?
flex-grow, flex-shrink, and flex-basis

What does flex: 1 equate to? 
flex-grow: 1, flex-shrink: 1, flex-basis: 0

What is the default direction for a flex container?
horizontal or row

How can you change the direction of a flexbox?
flex-direction: column

https://flexbox.malven.co/

How do you center a flexitem?
Add display: flex, align-items: center, and justify-content: center to the container element. Aligns childs 

What does justify-content do?
Aligns items horizontally

What does align-items do?
Aligns items vertically 

What does flex-direction do?
Defines the direction that itesm are placed in the container

What does align-content do?
Sets how multiple lines are spaced apart from each other
